<i>And if I die before I wake</i>

32:38.709 --> 32:40.502
<i>I pray the Lord my soul to take</i>

32:40.586 --> 32:42.713
<i>I pray the Lord my soul to take</i>

32:42.796 --> 32:46.133
<i>Hush, little baby, don't say a word</i>

32:46.717 --> 32:50.220
<i>And never mind that noise you heard</i>

32:50.804 --> 32:54.391
<i>It's just the monster under your bed</i>

32:54.474 --> 32:58.145
- <i>In your closet, in your head</i>
- <i>In your head</i>

32:58.228 --> 33:00.689
<i>Exit light</i>

33:02.149 --> 33:05.777
<i>Enter night</i>

33:05.861 --> 33:08.864
<i>Grain of sand</i>

33:10.157 --> 33:11.867
<i>We're off to never-never land</i>

33:22.419 --> 33:23.629
<i>No!</i>

33:25.881 --> 33:26.840
<i>No!</i>

33:28.967 --> 33:32.346
<i>What-- What if you went
so fast that smoke started coming out?</i>

33:32.429 --> 33:33.430
<i>Out of your ears.</i>

33:53.367 --> 33:55.869
Mark, sweetheart, are you all right?
I'm so sorry.

33:55.953 --> 33:57.829
- Yeah.
- I think I have this cystitis under--

33:57.913 --> 33:59.748
This was a mistake. I have to go.

33:59.831 --> 34:01.917
- Okay, well, let me come with you.
- No, that's not necessary.

34:02.000 --> 34:04.044
- No, I've paid my respects. Let's go.
- Let us pray.

34:04.127 --> 34:05.629
Our Father, who art in heaven…

34:07.381 --> 34:10.467
So, was the funeral just too sad, or--

34:12.844 --> 34:14.679
Something like that, yeah.

34:14.763 --> 34:16.264
If you ever wanna talk--

34:16.348 --> 34:20.226
Oh, no. Thank you. I just-- I'm fine.

34:22.062 --> 34:25.148
But thank you for, you know,
being my funeral buddy today.

34:26.733 --> 34:27.818
Good night.

34:28.360 --> 34:29.360
Good night.

37:27.456 --> 37:28.665
That's Petey?

37:30.918 --> 37:32.669
That's Petey.

37:34.796 --> 37:35.797
How did you--

37:35.881 --> 37:39.134
Would you mind taking that
up to diagnostics for me?

37:46.058 --> 37:47.100
Yes?

37:53.065 --> 37:54.942
You requested me, Ms. Cobel?

37:55.526 --> 38:01.281
Ms. Casey, I'd like you to run
a special wellness session with Mark S.

38:01.949 --> 38:02.950
Mark S.?

38:03.825 --> 38:05.244
What's the problem?

38:08.622 --> 38:11.458
He just needs it. Trust me.

38:26.139 --> 38:29.184
"Kier invites you to drink of his water."

38:30.310 --> 38:32.563
- Irving.
- Felicia said you'd be here.

38:35.649 --> 38:39.611
Is it awful to say
I don't care for that one?

38:40.112 --> 38:41.113
No.

38:41.864 --> 38:44.491
Honestly, it makes me nervous too.

38:46.827 --> 38:49.830
Such a lovely vista, but I keep thinking…

38:49.913 --> 38:51.123
He could slip.

38:54.960 --> 38:59.756
It was a thrill to have someone from MDR
come see us,

38:59.840 --> 39:02.426
to take an interest like you did, so…

39:03.552 --> 39:04.803
if I embarrassed myself--

39:04.887 --> 39:05.888
You didn't.

39:07.181 --> 39:09.349
Unless, you did?

39:10.350 --> 39:11.643
Are you embarrassed?

39:14.479 --> 39:15.480
No.

39:17.816 --> 39:18.817
Good.

39:21.528 --> 39:23.197
I have four more stops.

39:26.825 --> 39:29.077
Would MDR consider joining me?

39:31.788 --> 39:32.873
MDR would.

39:35.042 --> 39:36.043
You're crazy.

39:36.627 --> 39:38.378
I wish I could nap.

39:39.129 --> 39:41.590
I think I sleep 15 hours a night up there.

39:41.673 --> 39:42.925
It's a character flaw.

39:43.008 --> 39:45.219
It just means you're a party guy,
disco king.

39:45.302 --> 39:47.554
I can't be falling asleep, Burt.

39:47.638 --> 39:50.015
- Who cares?
- The handbook cares.

39:50.098 --> 39:53.936
"No workplace
shall be repurposed for slumber."

39:54.019 --> 39:58.482
I know the handbook, old man.
I'm more of a first edition guy.

39:59.942 --> 40:06.615
The original word of Kier: "And I shall
whisper to ye dutiful through the ages.

40:06.698 --> 40:10.536
In your noblest thoughts and epiphanies
shall be my voice.

40:10.619 --> 40:13.038
You are my mouth,

40:13.622 --> 40:17.125
and through ye, I will whisper on

40:17.209 --> 40:19.837
when I am 10 centuries demised."

40:22.714 --> 40:24.299
I don't understand.

40:24.383 --> 40:28.846
He doesn't just speak to us
through the handbook or the paintings.

40:29.638 --> 40:31.265
He finds other ways.

40:34.476 --> 40:36.270
"You think you need your job.

40:37.938 --> 40:40.315
But I've lived abroad as a vagrant,

40:40.399 --> 40:45.195
abstaining from my own money
to rely on the charity of strangers.

40:45.779 --> 40:49.700
Most were beggars themselves,
yet they were happy.

40:50.450 --> 40:53.370
And so, for that summer, was I.

40:55.330 --> 40:57.666
Your job needs you,

40:59.042 --> 41:01.211
not the other way around."

41:06.967 --> 41:09.303
<i>Safe travels, MDR.</i>

41:10.262 --> 41:12.472
Thanks, O&D.

41:30.824 --> 41:32.034
Mark?

41:33.702 --> 41:34.953
I'm gonna go.

41:35.037 --> 41:36.205
Do it.

41:36.288 --> 41:39.416
I'm working up till the bell. I think
I may still crush this thing tonight.

41:40.751 --> 41:41.835
I hope you do.

41:45.172 --> 41:46.173
See you soon.

42:48.485 --> 42:49.486
Knew it.

42:55.409 --> 43:00.497
Sometimes I ask people
to sculpt how they feel out of clay.

43:01.415 --> 43:03.417
Would you like to do that?

43:07.796 --> 43:08.797
<i>All right.</i>

43:40.245 --> 43:45.751
"'Destiny'. An acrostic poem experience
by the author, Ricken Hale."

44:07.147 --> 44:11.485
<i>"D is for dreaming,
the start of it all.</i>

44:17.032 --> 44:19.159
<i>E is for energy…</i>

44:21.161 --> 44:23.080
<i>breaking down walls.</i>

44:24.373 --> 44:26.625
S is for stewardship,

44:28.085 --> 44:30.295
<i>of home and of earth.</i>

44:34.132 --> 44:38.345
<i>T is for terror,
which gives us more worth.</i>

44:42.266 --> 44:44.184
<i>I is for eyes,</i>

44:45.644 --> 44:47.646
which observe us with love.

44:50.148 --> 44:52.693
<i>Until N, meaning newness,</i>

44:53.652 --> 44:55.946
<i>rains down from above.</i>

44:58.532 --> 44:59.533
<i>And Y.</i>

45:00.534 --> 45:03.245
<i>That's a question we needn't now ponder.</i>

45:04.496 --> 45:09.793
For destiny, friends,
shall deliver all yonder."

45:11.962 --> 45:13.755
Hey. How are you?

45:13.839 --> 45:15.132
Good.

45:15.215 --> 45:17.384
Yeah? Seems like
you're getting the hang of stuff here.

45:20.137 --> 45:21.346
Cool.
